text: Laiana Rodrigues (born 8 May 1982) is a Brazilian Paralympic sitting volleyball player. She is part of the Brazil women's national sitting volleyball team. She competed at the 2016 Summer Paralympics, 2015 Parapan American Games, and 2019 Parapan American Games. == References == Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Brazilian sitting volleyball players
